abstract: They took boxes filled with 28,578 pages of transcripts and other evidence collected during the inquiry.
snippet: They took boxes filled with 28,578 pages of transcripts and other evidence collected during the inquiry.
lead_paragraph: Their argument finished, the House managers made one last stab on Saturday morning to underscore the power of their impeachment case against President Trump by marching from the House to the Senate with boxes filled with 28,578 pages of transcripts and other evidence collected during their inquiry.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo cursed at a National Public Radio reporter and repeatedly "used the F-word" in a shouted diatribe after she questioned him about Ukraine and the ousted American ambassador to Kiev in an interview on Friday, the reporter said.

abstract: Lawyers for U.S. President Donald Trump told his Senate impeachment trial on Saturday that Democrats' efforts to remove the president from office would set a "very, very dangerous" precedent in an election year.
snippet: Lawyers for U.S. President Donald Trump told his Senate impeachment trial on Saturday that Democrats' efforts to remove the president from office would set a "very, very dangerous" precedent in an election year.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Lawyers for U.S. President Donald Trump told his Senate impeachment trial on Saturday that Democrats' efforts to remove the president from office would set a "very, very dangerous" precedent in an election year.
headline_main: Defense at Senate Trial Says Ousting Trump Would Be 'Massive Interference' in Election
headline_print_headline: Defense at Senate Trial Says Ousting Trump Would Be 'Massive Interference' in Election

abstract: The tweet underscores what his lawyers already know: that as they begin defending him, Mr. Trump will be watching.
snippet: The tweet underscores what his lawyers already know: that as they begin defending him, Mr. Trump will be watching.
lead_paragraph: President Trump was up early Saturday, lashing out at “lyin’ cheatin’ liddle’ Adam ‘Shifty Schiff” and other Democrats, starting what could be his Twitter play-by-play of his lawyers finally mounting a defense in his impeachment trial.
headline_main: Trump lashes out at his Democratic rivals.

abstract: In keeping with their combative client’s own style, President Trump’s lawyers plan to insist he did nothing wrong,
snippet: In keeping with their combative client’s own style, President Trump’s lawyers plan to insist he did nothing wrong,
lead_paragraph: In keeping with their combative client’s own style, President Trump’s lawyers plan not only to insist he did nothing wrong, but also to go after his accusers in unrelenting terms, painting them as partisans not prosecutors. The lawyers hope to turn the tables on the Democrats by hurling back at them some of the same allegations they have made against their client. By their account, the Democrats are the ones who are corrupt liars who sought foreign help and are now abusing their power to steal an election.
headline_main: White House team will go after Trump’s accusers in unrelenting terms.

abstract: An audio recording appeared to capture President Donald Trump calling in 2018 for the firing of the then U.S. ambassador to Ukraine, a key figure in the series of events that led to his impeachment, ABC News reported on Friday

abstract: President Donald Trump's lawyers plunged into his impeachment trial defense Saturday by accusing Democrats of striving to overturn the 2016 election, arguing that investigations of Trump's dealings with Ukraine have not been a fact-finding mission but a politically motivated effort to drive him from the White House.

headline_main: Trump Lawyers Argue Democrats Just Want to Overturn Election

headline_main: Trump Team Makes Its Impeachment Defense

abstract: White House lawyers plan to discuss in detail the Bidens, as well as to assail the F.B.I. for its surveillance of a onetime Trump campaign aide.
snippet: White House lawyers plan to discuss in detail the Bidens, as well as to assail the F.B.I. for its surveillance of a onetime Trump campaign aide.
lead_paragraph: President Trump faces two articles of impeachment, for abuse of power and obstruction of Congress, stemming from his effort to pressure Ukraine to announce investigations into his Democratic rivals while withholding nearly $400 million in congressionally approved security aid in what a government agency called a violation of law.
headline_main: Defense case may focus on the actions of the other side.

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump on Friday discussed the security of telecommunications networks with British Prime Minister Boris Johnson, the White House said, as Britain nears a decision on Huawei's role in the country's future 5G network.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump on Friday discussed the security of telecommunications networks with British Prime Minister Boris Johnson, the White House said, as Britain nears a decision on Huawei's role in the country's future 5G network.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump on Friday discussed the security of telecommunications networks with British Prime Minister Boris Johnson, the White House said, as Britain nears a decision on Huawei's role in the country's future 5G network.
headline_main: Trump Speaks With PM Johnson About Telecoms Security-White House
headline_print_headline: Trump Speaks With PM Johnson About Telecoms Security-White House
